52.8	A_Short_History_of_Nearly_Everything	A Short History of Nearly Everything	A Short History of Nearly Everything is a popular science book by American author Bill Bryson that explains some areas of science, using a style of language which aims to be more accessible to the general public than many other books dedicated to the subject. It was one of the bestselling popular science books of 2005 in the UK, selling over 300,000 copies.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/ed/Bill_bryson_a_short_history.jpg/200px-Bill_bryson_a_short_history.jpg
